orted: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cEverything has a summit, and the summit of the Quran is Surat al-Baqarah. It contains a verse which is the chief of the Quran, the verse of the Throne.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2878 Grade: Hasan li\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15946,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/09\/05\/ayat-al-kursi-greatest-verse\/","url_meta":{"origin":35161,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Ayat al-Kursi: Throne Verse is greatest in Quran","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 5, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ubayy ibn Ka\u2019b reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Abu Mundhir, do you know which verse in the Book of Allah with you is greatest?\u201d I recited, \u201cAllah! There is no God worthy of worship except Him, the Ever-Living, All-Sustaining,\u201d (2:255). The Prophet\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35027,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/24\/yahya-on-wara\/","url_meta":{"origin":35161,"position":5},"title":"Yahya on Wara\u2019: True piety is inwardly and outwardly","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 24, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn \u2018Alawiyyah reported: Yahya ibn Mu\u2019adh, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cPiety has